- **`proof_patterns/add_one_modified`** ŌĆö supplies the **`hax_<op>_def_<type>` unfold idiom** (private `theorem` rewriting `+?` into the overflow-conditional `if` form, then `if_neg`/`if_pos`). Target needs the analogous lemma for signed `-?` on `i64` (`Int64.subOverflow`) ŌĆö `add_one_modified` is the clearest blueprint for that bridge.

- **`proof_patterns/min_modified`** ŌĆö `hax_mvcgen [..] <;> bv_decide` plus `Or.inl`/`Or.inr` case-split for if-branch postconditions returning one of the inputs. Same branch-on-comparison skeleton the target's two postconditions will use.

- **`proof_patterns/clamp_modified`** ŌĆö total function defined by nested `if (ŌåÉ ... <? ...)` returning each branch's value verbatim, proved with `mvcgen [clamp]; all_goals grind`. Lightest-weight discharge to try first on the target's branches before falling back to the saturating_sub-style manual unfold.

## Gaps

- **No signed-integer (`i8`/`i32`/`i64`) example in the library.** Every overflow / no-overflow precedent is on `UInt8`/`UInt64`. The target is the first `i64` case ŌĆö there is no precedent for `Int64.subOverflow`, the `IntN.subOverflow_iff` lemma name, or the asymmetry of signed overflow (subtraction can overflow at both ends). Adding a signed overflow / signed-subtraction-no-overflow example would directly fill this.
